- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category as the paper deals with algorithmic problems related to string processing.

- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper involves combinatorial and discrete structures such as strings and their run-length encodings.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the problem of finding the longest common factor of strings, which is related to information compression and coding.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as one of the algorithms proposed in the paper uses a line sweep technique, which is commonly used in computational geometry.
